commit_message:
Fix mongodb idempotence

  - Fix mongodb idempotence.
    1) Mongodb first run initiate mongo master replicas.
    2) The second run on other instances automatically initiate
    mongodb slave
  - Fix Puppet fails when primary-mongo role and master host for replicaset of
    mongoDB are placed on the different controller nodes
    Closes-bug: #1475296
  - Fix mongodb authentication problem after the first run
    Closes-bug: #1478871
  - Partially fix Adding MongoDB nodes
    Partial-bug: #1308990

    This patch set contains changes in upstream module which will be
    proposed to upstream in 8.0 timeline according to bug
    https://bugs.launchpad.net/fuel/+bug/1475948

Change-Id: Ie34be251c2211d99afe81db3595b74867c548577

commit_message:
libvirt: enhance libvirt to set admin password

Libvirt 1.2.16 provides to set to the domain an user
password. This commit enhances Nova to use this new API
and let users request to set the admin password.
By default we will use root as user but if os_type windows
is specified we will use Administrator

Change-Id: I6bd2e67716222b3aa0d777d4a9411dc7c4a93a84
Implement: blueprint libvirt-set-admin-password

commit_message:
Directly assign node to an upgrade cluster

The patch adds method that assigns a node to an upgrade cluster without
deleting it from DB. This allows to keep ID of the node and IP addresses
assigned to it. The node is booted into the bootstrap image as soon as
it moves to an upgrade cluster.

Implements blueprint: nailgun-api-env-upgrade-extensions
Co-Authored-By: Artur Svechnikov <asvechnikov@mirantis.com>
Change-Id: If10fadd149a32317420778607146d9d12108d3f9

commit_message:
Use hiera_hash for rabbitmq in neutron task

hiera_hash enables deep merge of rabbit hash,
which needs to function to allow plugins to
override some fields.

Change-Id: I6859c5a323757236bfa9e8521d6853cee4ccae53
Closes-Bug: #1481782

commit_message:
Introduce extension to upgrade clusters

The patch adds an extension which implements the procedure of upgrading
clusters from one major release to another. As a first step of the
procedure the extension provides an ability to create a seed cluster
with the same settings as the original.

Implements blueprint: nailgun-api-env-upgrade-extensions
Change-Id: I22d51a3ffd51a7c88bdcbde0eef6f47b65def1c8

commit_message:
Validation of id values for volumes_roles_mapping

  Any string can be set as 'id' in 'volumes_roles_mapping' and validation of
  node's role on PUT-request passes without an error.

* Add an additional validation step into 'RoleValidator.validate_update'.
* Add unit tests for node roles validation.

Closes-Bug: #1467097

commit_message:
Fix translation sync with Transifex

Transifex now reserves glossary as part of the name, so rename it (as
done in transifex) to glossary-1.

Glossary is only used for openstack-manuals, so we do this change only
at that place.

reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 5196, 'name': 'Matthew Treinish', 'email': 'mtreinish@kortar.org', 'username': 'treinish'}, {'_account_id': 5263, 'name': 'Jeremy Stanley', 'display_name': 'fungi', 'email': 'fungi@yuggoth.org', 'username': 'fungi', 'status': 'missing, presumed fed'}, {'_account_id': 7118, 'name': 'Ian Wienand', 'email': 'iwienand@redhat.com', 'username': 'iwienand'}]
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-08-05 15:00:16.000000000', 'files': ['jenkins/scripts/run-docs.sh'], 'message': "Fix search for docs tox job in run-docs.sh

The run-docs.sh script was checking for a tox job using the tox
-l/--listenvs flag. However this only shows jobs that are listed in
the envlist variable in the tox.ini. The docs job is not normally put
in this variable because it's what is used to define the default set
of jobs run when you just run 'tox' without any args. This commit
changes the if check to search the entire tox config for any jobs
listed in the configuration labeled docs. This should pick up docs
tox jobs more reliably.

Change-Id: Ieeccba08fe7960206864723e6f13a10309cfacf3
"}]
commit_message:
Fix search for docs tox job in run-docs.sh

The run-docs.sh script was checking for a tox job using the tox
-l/--listenvs flag. However this only shows jobs that are listed in
the envlist variable in the tox.ini. The docs job is not normally put
in this variable because it's what is used to define the default set
of jobs run when you just run 'tox' without any args. This commit
changes the if check to search the entire tox config for any jobs
listed in the configuration labeled docs. This should pick up docs
tox jobs more reliably.

Change-Id: Ieeccba08fe7960206864723e6f13a10309cfacf3

commit_message:
Upgrade and downgrade based on revision existence

Before there was no way to upgrade to a specific revision, because the
revision passed to the manager was passed to all the plugins, some of
which failed to process it.

Add a new method to every plugin `has_revision`, which returns
whether the plugin has the revision. Use it in upgrade and
downgrade.

Change-Id: I89b02d7ad479da6bff3c492c88edfee9c19abc22
Closes-Bug: 1474067

commit_message:
Bumping up thread pool for rabbitmq-server

The default thread pool for rabbitmq-server is set to 30,
when there are more cores available we should be bumping
up this number higher for better performance.

Change-Id: Ie98fcd49a2dc35fd212e15d4d78a9a4c8c4e44bf
Closes-bug: 1472793

commit_message:
Add placeholders for all previous specs

This commit adds a placeholder with link to the new location for each of
the specs that were moved by the previous commit. It also adds a
"placeholder" file containing TOC-style references to the old
directories, and a link to this on the index page.

This is broken into two commits to preserve the history; git can't
recognize a rename and replace operation in the same commit.

Change-Id: Ieea08e7b477993baaca76b14210547e3e26c2935
Co-authored-by: Jim Rollenhagen <jim@jimrollenhagen.com>

  * Remove upstream pull request which state is uncertain
    https://github.com/puppetlabs/puppetlabs-mongodb/pull/194

Change-Id: I00e44fb474a47a01e8be5bc09752c0723a4e970c

commit_message:
Improvements for MongoDB replica set configuration

  * Remove upstream pull request which state is uncertain
    https://github.com/puppetlabs/puppetlabs-mongodb/pull/194
  * Implement mongorc file with admin credentials:
    - source credentials only if authentication is required for
      MongoDB shell commands
  * Improvements for work with replica:
    - don't try to initialize replica if one of the host has
      already initialized it (if we already have primary)
    - if authenticaion is enabled we should initialize replica
      from localhost
    - new MongoDB nodes can add yourself now to existing cluster
  * Now we should use one mongo_primary file for all MongoDB nodes,
    so another files could be removed
  * Change order for MongoDB nodes:
    1. Primary
    2. All another MongoDB slaves

Change-Id: I00e44fb474a47a01e8be5bc09752c0723a4e970c

commit_message:
Reorganize specs tree

* Move liberty -> approved
* Move completed liberty specs to liberty-implemented
* Move kilo -> kilo-implemented
* Move juno -> juno-implemented
* Move kilo-archive -> backlog (moving these to approved causes test
  failures because the template changed since kilo)
* Reword the header for the index page
* Update unit tests to look at the new "approved" folder

** NOTE **

This patch does not create placeholders in the previous locations
for each spec. This will be done in the following patch so that the
history is preserved. Both patches must be landed together so that web
links are not broken for long.

Change-Id: I61f02731150ea944eafaa8c6ea702210364b3478
Implements: blueprint feature-based-releases

commit_message:
added common name based filter for tables

In horizon most number of the tables have the name based client side filter.
All the tables are implementing the filter class individually,
but the logic and code is same in all the places.
Adding generic class for name based filter will remove lot of the duplicate code.

In this patch i have added the generic class and using it in all the vpn tables,
once it is accepted, we can remove the duplicate classes
and use the generic class everywhere.

Change-Id: Ie9c6bfaaffc72f8144fa36d450cce77b16fae64c
Implements: blueprint common-client-filter
Closes-Bug: #1427521

too (the first partition), in case ${data} is a whole disk.

I noticed that the create_user and grant_role actions did some
unneeded keystone CLI calls to get UUIDs for use as parameters on
subsequent CLI calls.  Instead we can just use the user or tenant
name directly and reduce the number of calls made and speed up the

commit_message:
Remove unecessary calls to keystone cli

I noticed that the create_user and grant_role actions did some
unneeded keystone CLI calls to get UUIDs for use as parameters on
subsequent CLI calls.  Instead we can just use the user or tenant
name directly and reduce the number of calls made and speed up the
converge a bit.

No change in functionality.

Change-Id: I93deb01d183d9d50098445676c5b49b0b6ae4fea
Closes-Bug: 1479517

commit_message:
Vagrant configuration generation now uses pymysql.

Sometime recently, ironic moved to pymysql. This actually requires
a different URL connection string for databases, which was not
updated in the autogenerated config. This fixes that.

commit_message:
Move Horizon to pure plugin loading only

The root cause of 1479018 was the mixed method for loading content in
horizon. This patch moves horizon to load purely from enabled files.
There are a couple of things that were required to allow this change.

1) Adding a mechanism, can_register() to horizon/base.py to handle the
configuration based loading checks that had been accumulating in the
panel.py files. This is an optional static method in Panel to
encapsulate such configuration (read settings) based panel loading
logic. And added testing for and documentation for this addition.

2) Create a numbering scheme for plugins. Moved the base dashboards to
_1000_project.py _2000_admin.py _3000_identity.py _5000_settings.py.
then populated the required panel_group and panel enabled files sparsely
in those ranges. The sparseness is to allow for future additions.
Additionally, I moved the already added Angular based panels next to
their Django counterparts.

Once the configuration loading was normalized, the bug reported in
1479018 was resolved and tests work with plugins panels in all
dashboards.

Close-Bug: #1479018
Partially implements: blueprint plugin-sanity

Change-Id: I657e7ce37b2593a901a859cebf3d6ff8ada91941

commit_message:
Fix boot from volume no LPAR issue

A recent change introduced a bug where the tasks wouldn't have the LPAR
UUID (because the VM wasn't created when the volume adapter was
created).  This change set reverts the behavior a bit to pass the
lpar_uuid in on the connect/disconnect volume actions.

Change-Id: I2d1bd49b7389870f1657dd52909a87d161127b40
Closes-Bug: 1481776

commit_message:
Fix a race condition in mon creation

In EL7 based systems there seems to be a race condition between the
creation of client.admin stub and the service startup.

The easy fix is to ensure that the stub is there before the mon exists.

Change-Id: I34924f85387388942b0a88e10155c5af73c32a6f

revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2015-08-03 20:54:31.000000000', 'files': ['manila/tests/share/drivers/test_generic.py', 'manila/share/drivers/generic.py'], 'message': 'Fix Generic driver share extend

When extending shares, the Generic share driver will extend
the underlying Cinder volume. It will consider this operation to
have finished once the volume status is "available".

In some cases, the volume status can be reported as active before
actually starting the extend operation. For this reason, attaching
the volume can fail as the volume would be in 'extending' state.

This patch fixes the issue by properly waiting for the volume
extend operation to finish, checking the volume size against the
expected size.

Change-Id: I02e4a42110e323dc295e20f9f07411a13fdcc236

commit_message:
Fix Generic driver share extend

When extending shares, the Generic share driver will extend
the underlying Cinder volume. It will consider this operation to
have finished once the volume status is "available".

In some cases, the volume status can be reported as active before
actually starting the extend operation. For this reason, attaching
the volume can fail as the volume would be in 'extending' state.

This patch fixes the issue by properly waiting for the volume
extend operation to finish, checking the volume size against the
expected size.

Change-Id: I02e4a42110e323dc295e20f9f07411a13fdcc236
Closes-Bug: #1479697

commit_message:
DVR: avoid connection hanging on floating ip associate

In DVR, when a floating ip is associated with a port, the current
connection to external network will be hung(and unresponsive).

The connection may be any TCP, UDP, ICMP connections which are
tracked in conntrack.

When floating ip is added, to avoid hanging, this patch will
clear the connection state and cut off the connection immediately.

DocImpact
Partial-Bug: #1456624
Change-Id: I9c6f7c52884a0ce5f5fa13eff8c535835df9678d

commit_message:
Initial non-eth0 admin net support.

We are able to replace in fuel-devops settings
networks order and set eth0 as device.
Then it will setup environment with desired
network structure.
Now method upate_nodes erases this setup.
After fixing it, we will be able to use
custom networks in system tests.

Works in conjunction with, but does not depend on:
"fuel-main" I9c46752632cd3c741f1036c7b7ea93f9b975bd0d;
"fuel-devops" I87db9734418347161f60b854c1619c253ac9ab97.

Change-Id: Id2d48d2bbcad701ac8e6e628be603c533e360ec6
Partial-Bug: #1439417

commit_message:
Fix handle_delete for zaqar queue

Now the call to client.queue() is wrapped in try-except clause,
but actually queue() doesn't make any calls to api and can't rise
any exception. Such behaviour can lead to UPDDATE_FAILED state of the
stack if the queue will not exist. Try to delete queue and then catch
appropriate exception.

Change-Id: I484bae099e3236d6b00ec5b3c2c562d971b7463e

commit_message:
VPNaaS: Create grenade plugin

Creates a grenade plugin that will be used to verify the upgrade of
VPNaaS databases between versions. Code will check that the q-vpn
process is running before and after the upgrade, and that any
migrations are performed successfully.

Created is_neutron_vpnaas_enabled(), so that Grenade will perform
the update actions. This will get called, when Grenade calls
"is_service_enabled neutron-vpnaas" and relies on a DevStack change
to convert the project name, neutron-vpnaas, to a callable function.

As part of upgrade step, the devstack plugin for neutron-vpnaas will
be used to install the latest code.

Change-Id: I726e07776da83ef8d1a10069475e18060ca0d4c9
Depends-On: Iffa9901e24adbacb581425c4b38c7e8cff0da9e8

commit_message:
Add mechanism for automated certificate renewals

This adds a mechanism for authorizing certificate renewals
in an automated fashion, by providing the certificate being
renewed and proof of possession of the private key as
authentication/authorization.

Implements: auto-cert-renewal
APIImpact: Add mechanism to auto-renew certificates
DocImpact: Add docs for mechanism to auto-renew certificates
SecurityImpact: Add mechanism to auto-renew certificates

Change-Id: I409ac9a604dac39e0a1ed3f704702089bca674f0

commit_message:
Rewording subprocess without shell finding

This commit changes the finding for subprocess without shell to
reinforce that using a subprocess without a shell isn't an issue
(it's not like you're supposed to use a shell!), rather in some
cases it can be helpful to audit these calls.

Change-Id: I9d923a51f23428ec6399742bb13feee79a97d9ea

commit_message:
Add generators for uuid and cephx

In order to become more advanced with the ceph modules, we need to more
precisely create some of the attributes like the cluster uuid or the user
cephx auth keys.

While we don't use these generators now, adding them is necessary to that
parallel development work can occur on the library side. Updates to the
fixtures will be proposed when the library modules are ready to integrate.

Change-Id: I82f917cdaf5053fc45cf6071f598fb82da43846a
Closes-bug: #1475759

commit_message:
Replace deprecated oslo_db sqalchemy EngineFacade to enginefacade

Now at oslo_db EngineFacade is deprecated. Instead of
oslo.db.sqlalchemy.enginefacade.LegacyEngineFacade use
oslo.db.sqlalchemy.EngineFacade.

https://github.com/openstack/oslo.db/blob/master/oslo_db/sqlalchemy/enginefacade.py#L830

commit_message:
Add support for Host header in REST queries

Can use host request headers if enable_host_header is set to true
in config file. If host header is not specified or host header is
turned off, it will use the default api_base_uri.

Also added unit tests.

Change-Id: Ia353c116485f3e7112bcfde11457cdf7fe006422
Closes-bug: 1446387

commit_message:
Fix bootproto string parser for interface config type

A split() lookup function had incorrect syntax, forcing
lookups to fall back to dhclient process lookup, which
means switching from dhcp back to static will show in
the UI as "DHCP" type alwys.

Change-Id: I4fa405276e0af745812c411948358e971cf7ee6b
Closes-Bug: #1481022

commit_message:
objects: remove tracked changes in NUMA objects

The JSON data stored in the database for the various NUMA objects
includes the 'nova_objects.changes' array, listing all properties
there were changed before the object was JSON-ified. This is
useless information and just bloats the size of the JSON data.

To remove this, reset changes before converting the NUMA objects
into primitive form.

Change-Id: I038c392dd2c6800222f4e769b56f816b2e2513ee

commit_message:
Use network roles data for assigning of VIPs

Additional information from VIPs description should be included into
VIPs data serialized for orchestrator in 7.0. It was correct in case of
using Neutron but it was not changed for Nova-Network case sinse 6.1.
NovaNetworkManager70 is introduced now and it provides the same VIPs
allocation as for NeutronManaget70 but without templates support.

Change-Id: Iddb1bb894e72084224a76d7de86c3ad57cf06b25
Closes-Bug: #1480202

commit_message:
Add vcenter_bvt test:

Deploy environment with vCenter as backend for glance and multiple clusters

        Scenario:
            1. Create cluster with vCenter support
            2. Add 5 nodes with following roles:
                Controller
                Controller
                Controller
                CinderVMDK
                Compute + Cinder
            3. Set Nova-Network VlanManager as a network backend
            4. Deploy the cluster
            5. Run network verification
            6. Run OSTF

        Duration: 2h

Change-Id: I63463fe21134f60423d9f06f10ba5a4db722d994
Closes-bug: #1474242

commit_message:
Added 'add_filters' to ClientMixin for GET vars

This adds the ability to filter collections via the add_filters method
on the ClientMixin class. It takes a filters dict and adds those
filters to the URL. Added to all functionaltests clients.

Change-Id: Ia4a6eb6bf2d3aa84e02420645975bc4207b0f09a

The security group support for the VMware-NSXv Neutron plugin
requires that the Neutron port update the actual VNIC index of
the instance.

This patch adds the support for updating the VNIC index for the
Neutron port. This is done in two places:
1. When the instance is spawned
2. If and when a port is attached to a running instance

The Neutron support for the extension is:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/144278

This is part of the blueprint vmware-nsxv-support

Change-Id: Ie990fa1141a7b2bdae1883572969adef072f4358

commit_message:
Neutron: add in API method for updating VNIC index

The security group support for the VMware-NSXv Neutron plugin
requires that the Neutron port update the actual VNIC index of
the instance.

This patch adds the support for updating the VNIC index for the
Neutron port. This is done in two places:
1. When the instance is spawned
2. If and when a port is attached to a running instance

The Neutron support for the extension is:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/144278

This is part of the blueprint vmware-nsxv-support

Change-Id: Ie990fa1141a7b2bdae1883572969adef072f4358

commit_message:
Truncate long names

This commit prevents page layout failure in the following cases:

1) In page headers at environment and  component details page
   and deployment page also

2) Current environment and category name at applications page

Also, environment name translation was removed since it is user input.
(and truncate doesn't work with blocktrance)

This is a cherry-pick from 0c98c671c8ba106d2aadc183a3c69cb6b08e0ea0
Closes-Bug: #1467489

Change-Id: Ie40113ece55456a7a72048939f8c1f57afde3212

commit_message:
Update environment details view

* Drop area is not a table row anymore, so it's not counted as an extra component and can not be filtered

* Hide drop area in case no applications available

* No components is displayed if there are no items in the table.
  Previously, drop area always be there

This is a cherry-pick from 8e2700228f0ecea862e66044497e32830c6ccb74

Change-Id: Ieca60bd4234a91b866f8c9adefe1afcd285c5546
Closes-Bug: #1467939

commit_message:
Warn user about unsupported content type

1) Raise exception to user when the specified content type is unsupported, instead
of silently replacing it to default type 'application/json'.
2) Renamed 'InvalidContentType' exception to more clear name
'UnsupportedContentType'.

Change-Id: Id336fc4360f451f3b8febfb453e7d0d119ab9b01
Closes-Bug: #1480036

commit_message:
Fixes Resource object refresh to use db object

Fix Resource object _refresh method to actually pass a database object
to _from_db_object, instead of wrapped one. This fixes properties
encryption.

Change-Id: I3d8d54fa7441c95fc3de5354f80ce2e7e2ba7054
Closes-Bug: #1481644

commit_message:
update cinder's key permission to allow nova snapshots

Preparing the field for this patch:

https://review.openstack.org/205282

The client.cinder key needs to have write permission to the glance pool
in order to complete the snapshot process.

Change-Id: I98f16167db864ffd14e8c3dd5dec81fc16245448

commit_message:
cleanup NovaObjectDictCompat from virtual_interface

cleanup subclassing on NovaObjectDictCompat and fix subsequent
tests and code associated with nova/objects/virtual_interface.py

Due to the exhaustive nature of changes, the cleanup is done
one object at a time.

This is the second patch of the series.
There shall be more patches to follow for other objects.

Related to blueprint liberty-objects

commit_message:
libvirt: Add logging for dm-crypt error conditions

This change adds logging for errors related to dm-crypt (used for
ephemeral storage encryption). Unit tests are included for the various
failure conditions as well as to ensure that the errors are logged.

Co-Authored-By: Daniel Genin <Daniel.Genin@jhuapl.edu>

Change-Id: I47b68053df876e3504e41aed56c94cf302f5d616

commit_message:
Activate pep8 check that _ is imported

Remove the specification in tox.ini that _ is a builtin so that
it will no longer assume that _ does not need to be imported.
This helps ensure that the _ from i18n is used.

Activating this check did not flag any violations.

Change-Id: Id555b593cff19d7c741b4233182837def685317a

commit_message:
Base trigger implementation

This patch adds base class for triggers. A trigger can be a ceilometer
alarm or a monasca alarm or a message queue, for example.

This patch also added missing function calls in the db api layer.

Change-Id: Ic3827c5dc697426a4c3b9a57ab3dabdcdd1bc156

commit_message:
Handle None actions in Alarm.delete_actions

Recent trust change introduced a regression where it expected a list in
alarm deletion, but can get a None value. This patch fixes it.

Change-Id: I89f391b8d0e0f80174a58e3826339242e27981b5
Closes-Bug: #1481642

commit_message:
OS::Cinder::VolumeType help doc string contains redundant info

All resource types except the volumetype is provided without example template.
But volumeType is provided with example, which is not consistent with other
resource types and it introduce maintenance overheat.
This patch remove the example template provided in the doc string
of heat/engine/resources/openstack/cinder/cinder_volume_type.py

Change-Id: Ic7f2a2f2a289f52486551770187cf3def8a4b942

commit_message:
libvirt: rework quiesce to not share "sensitive" informations

We do not want to share with user that the version of libvirt
or hypervisor type.
This commit also introduces a generic exception to handle the case
where the image does not provide the guest agent flag.

Change-Id: Ibb37639d5a5ad06eaf25e82af8726dd8ce13221d

commit_message:
MongoDB databases and users not created on create

When creating an instance, databases and users can be specified to also
be created. MongoDB currently ignores them. The guest's prepare method
should create the given databases and users.

Change-Id: I8bf0062d522d5f5eeea72880b0671e75b929a4fd
Closes-bug: #1480413

commit_message:
Register existing user for deployment

Rally supports two ways of getting users:
- Autocreation using 'users' context
- Registering users with deployment

And two ways of registering deployment:
- From env
- From file

And for the moment, registered deployment by devstack does not have registered
users that could be used by tasks that expect such. Same for registration using
existing env vars.

So, add existing admin user to registered users to able be to run tasks and add
task samples without 'users' context.

Change-Id: I12ffebede5eeaecf488deded78bf48ab4d43d54a
Closes-Bug: #1465302

commit_message:
Remove simple scheduler which is deprecated since Juno

Chance and Simple scheduler functionality can be archived using
FilterScheduler, config details is described here:
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/cinder/api/cinder.scheduler.simple.html
The implementation has been deprecated in Juno,so we can remove
it safely now.

DocImpact

commit_message:
Pin requirements to versions from Kilo

Updated version of upper packages bounds to be more in line
with those from Kilo's global requirements.
This solved some of the problems with constantly breaking
releases of new OSt & oslo packages.
Unfortunately not all of them are in line still so we need pinning
for example inc ase of stevedore.

Change-Id: Iefa3628af5ae86414082b7100a671544b354e355
Partial-Bug: #1481212

commit_message:
Update link to baremetal provisioning in rst file

The link to baremetal under the hypervisors section of the Cloud Administrator Guide
points to a depreciated page for nova baremetal, instructing users to go to the Ironic
baremetal provisioning page instead. The fix updates the baremetal link within the Cloud
Admin Guide to go directly to the Ironic page.

Change-Id: I968b3cf328af8f65658b194aaeaef8fca7ad97e8
Closes-Bug: #1478628

commit_message:
Ignore inet6 if IP_VERSION==4

Even if IP_VERSION=4 is specified, IP_BRD is overwritten by invalid value in
inet6 in _move_neutron_addresses_route(). This change makes it doesn't use
inet6 field if IP_VERSION=4 is specified.

Closes-Bug: #1481639
Change-Id: I06419c785627858d05ded96fa1f66bcbc59c066a

commit_message:
Pretty JSON when logging

It's hard for human read structured data without formatting.
For now OSTF results, tasks, build information printed in logs
in one line and serialized. This patch format such data
with json.dumps(str, indent=1)

Change-Id: Ib51eff02a7c2b707d0d60605f7b397adc72f6f5e
Closes-Bug: #1480186

commit_message:
Remove compatibility workaround in reboot plugin test

Previously some code was added to old plugins for compatibility
with Fuel 7.0. But now FuelPluginBuilder is up to date, so
workaround have to be removed because it fail test.

Change-Id: I4fc93574a5a2bd4d8fd39965b8590ee7f61ba978
Closes-Bug: #1480201

commit_message:
Adding NFS support to the GPFS Driver

This change helps create cinder volumes on a GPFS cluster,
when the cinder services are not running directly on one of
the GPFS nodes.

The NFS export created on GPFS cluster will be locally mounted
on a node running the cinder service. The cinder volume service
will communicate with GPFS nodes over SSH to execute CLIs remotely.

This change also ports the GPFSDriver to ABC driver model.

Implements : blueprint ibm-gpfs-nfs-support

DocImpact

Needs an update in gpfs driver documentation, as this patch
adds an NFS based access for GPFS cinder driver.

Change-Id: I40e5098482d48552170c34e74be0c9e2f544fef5
